places.name: Jama Masjid Jalali
places.address: V782+MXC Jama Masjid Jalali, Mohalla Abulfazl, Jalali, Uttar Pradesh 202128

featured_reviews.review_id: An important landmark in Jalali is the historic Jama Masjid which was built by Sultan Ghyasuddin Balban in that is taken care by Sayyids of Jalali. It was built by Sultan Ghiyasuddin Balban in 665 Hijri. The masjid bears an inscription with the name of Balban dated 665 Hijri or 1267 AD.  The mosque was renovated and rebuilt by Haji Syed Mehdi Ali of Jalali in 1901. An account of the contributions of Haji Mehdi Ali is engraved in Persian on the marble stone which forms part of the middle arch of the mosque.

featured_reviews.review_id: Jama masjid important landmark in Jalali is the historic Jama Masjid that is taken care by Sayyids of Jalali. It was built by Sultan Ghiyasuddin Balban and is over 751 years old. The masjid bears an inscription with the name of Balban dated 665 Hijri or 1267 AD. The mosque is well maintained and is looked after by a trustee appointed by Shia Waqf Board, Lucknow. The photograph of the mosque and its brief history along with the inscriptions of Sultan Balban.
